    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_11_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_11",
      "description": "Presenting a showroom-grade 2001 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S) Series 8. This mechanical masterpiece features the iconic 13B-REW power plant, utilizing its sequential twin-turbocharger system to deliver linear torque and a visceral high-RPM surge. The drivetrain is anchored by a crisp five-speed manual transmission and a factory Torsen limited-slip differential for surgical power delivery. Every bushing, vacuum line, and cooling passage remains in peak operational status, ensuring the legendary 50/50 weight distribution and double-wishbone suspension geometry perform exactly as engineered. Compression test results are verified and uniform across all rotor faces, confirming the absolute integrity of the apex seals. This is a zero-compromise, collector-grade example of JDM engineering excellence.",
